00:29:00.030 --> 00:29:04.750
The operations cards
are amazingly clever.

00:29:04.750 --> 00:29:06.020
They were quite small cards.

00:29:06.020 --> 00:29:12.760
A single hole would then
rotate these barrels

00:29:12.760 --> 00:29:15.220
to a certain position.

00:29:15.220 --> 00:29:17.450
There's actually
three sets of barrels,

00:29:17.450 --> 00:29:21.950
and each of the barrels has
50 or 80 rows of pegs around.

00:29:21.950 --> 00:29:23.870
So a single hole in
an operations card

00:29:23.870 --> 00:29:25.840
could activate dozens
and dozens of levers,

00:29:25.840 --> 00:29:28.600
which is what you need
to run an operation.

00:29:28.600 --> 00:29:30.620
The machine could do
basically four things.

00:29:30.620 --> 00:29:33.990
It could add, subtract,
multiply, divide.

00:29:33.990 --> 00:29:36.520
Any more complicated
mathematical thing

00:29:36.520 --> 00:29:39.020
you did, you would have to be
very clever in the programming

00:29:39.020 --> 00:29:43.986
end, break it down into
those four operations,

00:29:43.986 --> 00:29:45.235
run it down a string of cards.

00:29:49.690 --> 00:29:52.100
So all those levers are
activated, and what they do

00:29:52.100 --> 00:29:55.350
is they then engage
all the levers

00:29:55.350 --> 00:29:56.582
at one of these sections.

00:29:56.582 --> 00:29:58.290
Basically, each of
these little sections,

00:29:58.290 --> 00:30:01.320
this is just a cartoon version.

00:30:01.320 --> 00:30:03.490
All these little sections
are beautifully worked out

00:30:03.490 --> 00:30:05.265
and extremely complicated.

00:30:05.265 --> 00:30:06.640
But each of these
little sections

00:30:06.640 --> 00:30:11.585
does a specific thing,
adding or carrying ones.

00:30:11.585 --> 00:30:12.960
If you were
multiplying a number,

00:30:12.960 --> 00:30:15.840
it would break it up into
multiply by 1, multiply by 2,

00:30:15.840 --> 00:30:20.070
multiply by 3, into all
these sections for speed.

00:30:20.070 --> 00:30:22.530
So it basically
engages that section

00:30:22.530 --> 00:30:24.860
so it's all ready to go.

00:30:24.860 --> 00:30:29.830
Then the variable card, which
is the third kind of card,

00:30:29.830 --> 00:30:32.540
this is the addressing
system, basically.

00:30:32.540 --> 00:30:35.790
It then says, OK, pick up
from address number one,

00:30:35.790 --> 00:30:37.600
engages the rack.

00:30:37.600 --> 00:30:39.280
The rack slides
off into what you

00:30:39.280 --> 00:30:42.930
call the ingress axis, which
is this one at the front here.

00:30:45.410 --> 00:30:45.910
Sorry.

00:30:45.910 --> 00:30:47.890
I'm pointing, which
you can't see.

00:30:47.890 --> 00:30:49.640
So this is the
position in the store,

00:30:49.640 --> 00:30:52.545
so it actively reads out to
the passive ingress axis.

00:30:55.350 --> 00:30:58.984
Then that engages the big
central wheel possibly.

00:30:58.984 --> 00:31:01.150
I mean, this is all much
more complicated, actually.

00:31:01.150 --> 00:31:05.390
There's way more bits
than I'm showing here.

00:31:05.390 --> 00:31:07.880
And then this becomes
active and reads the number

00:31:07.880 --> 00:31:12.576
off into whatever section
has been indicated,

00:31:12.576 --> 00:31:13.575
reads the second number.

00:31:16.880 --> 00:31:19.340
So now it's got both numbers,
and then it does a thing,

00:31:19.340 --> 00:31:21.990
basically.

00:31:21.990 --> 00:31:24.800
Each of these little bits
is very, very specialized

00:31:24.800 --> 00:31:29.650
for a specific
arithmetical thing.

00:31:29.650 --> 00:31:31.630
You'll notice the barrels
are turning around.

00:31:31.630 --> 00:31:33.260
The barrel would
have, basically,

00:31:33.260 --> 00:31:36.090
a little program
in wedges around.

00:31:36.090 --> 00:31:38.740
So once you set it up
with one operations card,

00:31:38.740 --> 00:31:40.925
then it runs through a
little micro program.

00:31:40.925 --> 00:31:45.470
[MECHANICAL SOUND] That's
